BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Nature Walk": Music and Science Come Together
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260412T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260412T150000
UID:2604051rKBUDMwIE6mELoQ2HrjSA
DESCRIPTION:As a prelude to the gallery show reception for “Art as Inqui
 ry\, ” the IU Jacobs School of Music Student Composer Association perfor
 ms "Nature Walk" starting at 2 pm.  It is a musical and narrative perform
 ance led by four composers\, with narration and visuals by Distinguished I
 U Biology Professor Roger Hangarter. This unique musical performance depic
 ts the seasonal re-awakening of nature in southern Indiana. Dr. Hangarter
  has led IU Student composers on a hike where they observed life in ponds
  and fields\, then composed musical pieces based on their experiences duri
 ng the hike. \n\nAt 3 pm\, refreshments are available and prizes for artwo
 rk shown in “Art as Inquiry” will be awarded. This gallery show featur
 es 2 D and 3 D artworks from 25 artists across several states\, inviting v
 isitors to encounter climate research and climate unease\, ecological chan
 ge\, and environmental justice through the lens of artistic imagination.
LOCATION:Pillar Arts Alliance Center
URL:https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/nature-walk-4-12-2026/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
