UID:26040502WyD1_cU02dwMEHyYz0lg
DESCRIPTION:All ages are invited to explore “Art as Inquiry\,” a jurie
 d climate art exhibition at the Pillar Arts Alliance Center\, Bloomington\
 , IN from Apr 2–29. This gallery show\,  “Art as Inquiry”\, feature
 s 2 D and 3 D artworks from 25 artists across several states\, inviting vi
 sitors to encounter climate research and climate unease\, ecological chang
 e\, and environmental justice through the lens of artistic imagination.\n\
 nThis reception begins with "Nature Walk\," a musical performance\, starti
 ng at 2 pm.  It is a musical and narrative performance led by IU Jacobs S
 chool of Music student Thejas Mirle and four composers\, with narration by
  Distinguished IU Biology Professor Roger Hangarter.\n\nAt 3 pm\, refreshm
 ents are available and prizes for artwork will be awarded.
LOCATION:Pillar Arts Alliance Center
URL:https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/art-as-inquiry-reception/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
