BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:“Art as Inquiry\,” A Gallery Show
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260418T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260418T180000
UID:260324DCU_3vkK_Em-Lvo6h0HeXA
DESCRIPTION:**Artists for Climate Awareness invites people of all ages to 
 experience “Art as Inquiry\,”** a juried climate‑art exhibition on v
 iew **April 2–29** at the Pillar Arts Alliance Center in Bloomington\, I
 N and online. Featuring 2‑D and 3‑D works from artists across several 
 states\, this Earth Month exhibition explores urgent climate and environme
 ntal issues through creative expression and community engagement.\n\nArt\,
  especially\, can turn scientific knowledge into experiences that resonate
  emotionally—offering insights that facts and figures alone can’t alwa
 ys reach. When these perspectives come together\, they open up fresh ways 
 of seeing and help people connect more deeply with complex ideas. “Art a
 s Inquiry” invites visitors to encounter climate research\, ecological c
 hange\, and environmental justice through the lens of artistic imagination
 .\n\nBeginning **April 19**\, artwork from the **Climate Co‑lab** (Brush
 es for a Better Planet) joins the exhibition\, displayed alongside the Art
  as Inquiry works.\n\n**Earth Month Events (Free\; Public Invited):**\n\n*
 *April 12\, 2–3 pm** – *Nature Walk*\, a musical and narrative perform
 ance led by IU Jacobs School of Music student Thejas Mirle and four compos
 ers\, with narration by Distinguished IU Biology Professor Roger Hangarter
 .\n\n**April 12\, 3–5 pm** – Reception for the member climate‑art ex
 hibition\; prizes awarded. 🌱\n\n**April 19\, 3–6 pm** – Climate Co
 ‑lab Reception + *Nature Walk* performance\; brief introductions of arti
 sts and partners.\n\n**Gallery Hours:** • **Thu–Sat: 2–8 pm** • **
 Sun: 12–6 pm** Pillar Arts Alliance Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington.
  Free admission.
LOCATION:Pillar Arts Alliance Center
URL:https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/climate-co-lab/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
