BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:RECEPTION and Music for Gallery Show: Climate Co-Lab\, and Art as 
 Inquiry
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260419T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260419T170000
UID:260405ityzsjkJ2kyJNF7_I1zUPA
DESCRIPTION:Discover “Climate Co‑lab\,” part of “Art as Inquiry\,
 ” an inspiring exhibition of 2‑D and 3‑D artwork presented at the  
 Pillar Arts Alliance Center in the College Mall\, Bloomington\, IN. The re
 ception showcases work created by six artists and a group of musicians col
 laborating with Indiana University scientists\, and who have translated th
 eir shared research outings into art. After a short introduction at 3pm\, 
 a group of composers and musicians from Indiana University will perform N
 ature Walk\, a musical and visual presentation inspired by an early spring
  outing led by Distinguished IU Biology Professor Roger Hangarter. This 
 unique performance depicts the seasonal re-awakening of nature in southern
  Indiana.\n\nFollowing the performance\, visitors are invited to enjoy ref
 reshments and experience the artworks of the Brushes for a Better Planet C
 o-Lab project along with invited artwork in a larger show\, “Art as Inqu
 iry\,” by 25 Artists for Climate Awareness members. The project is Artis
 ts for Climate Awareness-hosted and organized by Lily Shan with Brushes fo
 r a Better Planet.
LOCATION:Pillar Arts Alliance Center
URL:https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/reception-climate-co-lab/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
