BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Saving Ava
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260429T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260429T213000
UID:260203ZfzWZbbG7U-ipz5bXCt6Ww
DESCRIPTION:The biggest independent film to ever be made on IU’s campus.
  A pulpy adventure inspired by the films of John Hughes and Rob Reiner\, s
 ix teenagers set out on a cross-country journey through the Midwest to fin
 d their missing friend. As the miles pass\, old tensions from the turbulen
 t transition between high school and college resurface. Somewhere in betwe
 en growing up and settling down\, a backdrop of summer crickets\, endless 
 blue skies\, and open roads\, they confront their memories and missteps th
 at shaped their drifting friendships.\n\nThis film is family friendly. (In
 cludes depictions of alcohol consumption.)
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://buskirkchumley.org/events/saving-ava-april-29-2026/
X-SOURCE:Limestone Post
END:VEVENT
